The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 December is 116,203 (13,393.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 November, there were 5,415 new confirmed cases (624.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 November, there were 5,373 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (42 extra cases).
